.TH _PRINTF 3
.SH NAME
_printf - custom implementation of the printf function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "main.h"
.br
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf()
function produces output according to a
.I format
string and a variable number of arguments.

Format specifiers include:
.TP
.B %c
Prints a single character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a null-terminated string.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints a signed integer.

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon success, the number of characters printed is returned.
If an error occurs, the function returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
_printf("Hello %s", "YUMMERS");
_printf("Number: %d", 42);
.fi

